The police in Rivers State have arrested four suspected kidnappers for allegedly killing their victim and taxi driver, Onyekachi Obioma Chukwuagu. The police also recovered Chukwuagu’s abandoned corpse along the East/West Road close to Rumuodogo 1 Community in Emohua Local Government Area of the State. The acting Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Grace Iringe-Koko in a statement on Sunday identified the suspects and their ages as Obichi Ngita, 20; Chisom Honest, 20; Young Chitu, 21 and Omens Woke, 23. The statement said the suspects on March 22, posed as regular passengers and boarded the victim’s vehicle.   JUST IN: Adamu, NWC members take oath of office     2022 NUGA: Two Gold medalists publicly announce marriage…     APC convention: Voting, results announcement ends   The police said: “However, when they got to a quiet part of the route, they kidnapped the victim and abandoned the vehicle, with Reg. No. GDD 250 MU by the roadside. “The command upon receipt of the complaint swiftly mobilised operatives to the scene where they cordoned off the area and commenced an intensive search resulting in the arrest of Chisom Honest, who led operatives to the rest of the gang, and the location of the victim’s corpse. “The suspects claimed they murdered the victim, using a machete, for refusing to cooperate with them. Efforts are being intensified to apprehend other suspects indicted in the matter with a view to concluding the investigations. “The Commissioner of Police, while consoling the family of the deceased, assured that the suspects would be arraigned in court on completion of investigation in line with his commitment to the cause of justice”.